There are doors to the north, south, east and west.

counter, containing knives, an Arms Dealer stands, polishing a new
sword.

description: You stand in a large hall, the hall of the Magitek.  Several doors
in this room lead to other rooms of the stronghold.  Above, a large
skylight lets in the sun's rays, and the star's light.  A large
bubbling pool stand in the center of the room, under the skylight.
The walls have a large bench jutting out of them, allowing members to
sit and socialize.  To the north, you see a door that says "ARMS".  To
the south, you see the "Chamber Of Transportation".  To the west is
the Meeting Hall.

description: You step in to a well organized shop filled with all sorts of
armor, weapons and other valubles.  You do not see any dust or dirt in
the store.  Jerald, the broker, must keep good care of all of his
items.  You almost feel like just standing in one place in awe and for
fear of hurting any of the valubles.

as tall as the ceiling towers before you, awaiting the hall.  The
Vectorian Flag hangs over the doorways.

of the room, a dim lamp fills the room with a dark glow.  Newspaper
articles hang on the wall, and some maps line the desk against the
wall.  You stand within WarHammer's Room.
